com/2013/04/25/whats-new-with-startbox-2-7/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/25/whats-new-with-startbox-2-7/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 25 Apr 2013 19:34:18 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Startbox";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=7337";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:445:"Since it&#8217;s development in 2010, the StartBox Theme Framework has been actively updated and upgraded allowing it to grow into a fierce WordPress theme framework. WebDevStudios and StartBox lead developer Brian Richards have been hard at work to continue to maintain the quality &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/25/whats-new-with-startbox-2-7/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3015:"<p><a href="http://wpstartbox.com/"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-7338" alt="sb2.7-200x200-tc" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/sb2.7-200x200-tc.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a>Since it&#8217;s development in 2010, the <a href="http://wpstartbox.com/" target="_blank">StartBox Theme Framework</a> has been actively updated and upgraded allowing it to grow into a fierce WordPress theme framework. WebDevStudios and StartBox lead developer <a title="Brian Richards" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-richards/">Brian Richards</a> have been hard at work to continue to maintain the quality product you already love and we want to highlight the changes that have been made with <a href="http://wpstartbox.com/2013/03/29/startbox-2-7-now-available/">version 2.7</a>.</p>\n<h4>Image-Sizing Updates</h4>\n<p>Prior to 2.7 Startbox was using TimThumb for image resizing. We have now changed over to use the native WordPress resizing functionality.</p>\n<h4>Language Support</h4>\n<p>You can now use StartBox in a number of different languages. With added language support, you can view StartBox in British English, German, French, Italian, Spanish, Russian, Brazilian Portuguese, and Japanese. This support is built right in!</p>\n<h4>Slideshow Phase-Out</h4>\n<p>The built in slideshow function will be removed in StartBox 2.8 and in 2.7 the feature has been disabled by default. This has been done because we believe that there are a number of great slideshow plugins out there and recommend using one of them.</p>\n<p>Sites with slideshows already enabled will continue to display them and you will still be able to use the Startbox slideshow by following the instructions below. A plugin with the Startbox slideshow code will be released so you can still use slideshows on your site.</p>\n<blockquote><p><strong>If you want to continue using Slideshows on new sites with StartBox 2.7, you can do so by running <code>add_theme_support( ''sb-slideshows'' );</code> on the <code>''after_setup_theme''</code> hook.</strong></p></blockquote>\n<h4>Bug fixes</h4>\n<p>With any theme framework there will be the occasional bug or two. We have been working hard to fix bugs as they show up to assure our customers they are working with a quality product.</p>\n<blockquote><p>We fixed a rather nasty bug with the custom sidebars implementation that prevented more than one custom sidebar appearing on any given page at the same time. We fixed another bug with loop.php and single.php that prevented articles with pagination from showing their pagination. Finally, we fixed the author template archive to actually return the full archive of posts, instead of just the most recent one. &#8211; Brian Richards</p></blockquote>\n<p>You can <a href="https://github.com/WebDevStudios/StartBox/blob/master/changelog.txt">view the change log</a> for StartBox 2.7 or you can always <a href="https://github.com/WebDevStudios/StartBox">download a completely free version of StartBox</a> on GitHub.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/25/whats-new-with-startbox-2-7/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Lisa Sabin-Wilson and Shayne Sanderson at WordCamp Minneapolis 2013!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:106:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/24/lisa-sabin-wilson-and-shayne-sanderson-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013-2/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:115:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/24/lisa-sabin-wilson-and-shayne-sanderson-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013-2/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 24 Apr 2013 16:13:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordCamp";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=7377";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:402:"If you keep up with our blog, you already know that Lisa is speaking twice at WordCamp Minneapolis this year. What you may not know, is that she is not the only WDS team member going to the event. Our &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/24/lisa-sabin-wilson-and-shayne-sanderson-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013-2/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1788:"<p>If you keep up with our <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/blog/">blog</a>, you already know that <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa</a> is speaking twice at <a href="http://2013.minneapolis.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Minneapolis</a> this year. What you may not know, is that she is not the only WDS team member going to the event. Our Project Manager, <a title="Shayne Sanderson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/shayne-sanderson/">Shayne Sanderson</a>, will also be attending!</p>\n<p>Shayne was recently just added to the WDS team at the beginning of year, as our Technical Project Manager. His job is to help our clients and our developers/designers work together to create a successful and easy going relationship. He has been working with WordPress since 2006 and has spoken/attended too many WordCamps to list. He&#8217;s an avid learner and teacher of all things WordPress!</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re going to be attending the event this weekend, running from Friday April 26th until Sunday, April 28th, make sure you drop by and say hello to Lisa and Shayne!</p>\n<p>The organizers have put together an awesome roster of speakers, including Lisa, this year. To see who you can learn from, make sure you check out their <a href="http://2013.minneapolis.wordcamp.org/speakers/">speakers page</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, don&#8217;t miss out on the <a href="http://2013.minneapolis.wordcamp.org/buddycamp/">BuddyCamp</a> that will be held on Sunday &#8211; you are promised food.. and you can&#8217;t argue with food.</p>\n<p>To view the talks that Lisa will be giving, you can view <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/19/lisa-sabin-wilson-speaking-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013/">our previous blog post about her presentations</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:111:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/24/lisa-sabin-wilson-and-shayne-sanderson-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013-2/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:51:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"Lisa Sabin Wilson speaking at WordCamp Minneapolis 2013";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:92:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/19/lisa-sabin-wilson-speaking-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/19/lisa-sabin-wilson-speaking-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 19 Apr 2013 17:09:02 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"BuddyPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"General";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordCamp";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=7363";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:420:"Add another one to the resume! Lisa is speaking this year at WordCamp Minneapolis. The event is being held Saturday April 27th &#8211; Sunday April 28th. On Saturday it will take place at MCTC in downtown Minneapolis, and on Sunday, &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/19/lisa-sabin-wilson-speaking-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3249:"<p>Add another one to the resume! <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa</a> is speaking this year at <a href="http://2013.minneapolis.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Minneapolis</a>. The event is being held Saturday April 27th &#8211; Sunday April 28th. On Saturday it will take place at <a href="http://www.minneapolis.edu/">MCTC</a> in downtown Minneapolis, and on Sunday, it will take place at the <a href="http://www.hclib.org/AgenciesAction.cfm?agency=Ce">Minneapolis Central Library</a>. She will be speaking twice at this event and as always, she is excited to share her knowledge.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/minneapolis.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-7373" alt="minneapolis" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/minneapolis.png" width="970" height="184" /></a></p>\n<p>Her first talk will be held at 3:00 PM on Saturday<br />\n<strong>&#8220;Scoping projects to avoid stress, headaches, and angry mobs&#8221;</strong></p>\n<div>\n<blockquote><p>Attention to detail in your code and design work is important – but before you lay down one single pixel, install your first plugin or one single line of code, you need to make sure that everyone (you, your client, your clients client, etc) are on the same page and make sure you are managing expectations on what the desired project outcome is. Learn how to dissect projects – either web site or plugin development – to determine the best approach to meet your client needs.</p>\n<p>This 30-40 minute covers hard lessons I’ve learned in a decade of client work – I hope to pass those headaches on to you so you don’t make the same mistakes. Q/A welcome, afterwards.</p></blockquote>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/buddycamp-widget-header.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-7374" alt="buddycamp-widget-header" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/buddycamp-widget-header.png" width="243" height="145" /></a>Also this year in Minneapolis, they are holding a <a href="http://2013.minneapolis.wordcamp.org/buddycamp/">BuddyCamp</a>. This portion of the event showcases all things BuddyPress, where you can learn how to integrate social networking into your website. Lisa&#8217;s second talk will be held during this portion.</p>\n<p>Her second talk with be held at 12:00 PM on Sunday.<br />\n<strong>&#8220;Intro to Building Online Communities with BuddyPress&#8221;</strong></p>\n<blockquote><p>An introductory look at the BuddyPress plugin for WordPress. Discover what BuddyPress is and determine if the features of the BuddyPress plugin meet your feature needs. This session takes you through a quick discovery of the features and components of BuddyPress, a walk through on installation and real world examples of BuddyPress in action. By the end of this session, you’ll have a complete grasp on what BuddyPress is (and isn’t) to enable you to answer the questions “Do I really need it?” and “How hard is it to work with?”</p></blockquote>\n<p>Make sure you check out the event and learn all you can! You can register <a href="http://2013.minneapolis.wordcamp.org/register/">here</a>.</p>\n</div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:97:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/19/lisa-sabin-wilson-speaking-at-wordcamp-minneapolis-2013/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"WordSesh 2013 – 24 Hours of WordPress!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/11/wordsesh-2013-24-hours-of-wordpress/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/11/wordsesh-2013-24-hours-of-wordpress/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 11 Apr 2013 19:26:05 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"WordSesh";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=7339";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:426:"WordSesh 2013 is an exciting new event for WordPress users everywhere! For the first time in history, there will be a 24 hour &#8211; you heard me &#8211; A 24-hour, non-stop WordPress extravaganza! What exactly is this magical event? WordSesh is basically &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/11/wordsesh-2013-24-hours-of-wordpress/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3628:"<p><a href="http://wordsesh.org/">WordSesh 2013</a> is an exciting new event for WordPress users everywhere! For the first time in history, there will be a 24 hour &#8211; you heard me &#8211; A <strong>24-hour, </strong>non-stop WordPress extravaganza!</p>\n<h3><span style="color: #808080"><strong><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/wordsesh.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-7340" alt="wordsesh" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/wordsesh-300x189.jpg" width="300" height="189" /></a><span style="color: #888888">What exactly is this magical event?</span></strong></span></h3>\n<p>WordSesh is basically the online version of WordCamp minus the BBQ lunch and after party. The event will consist of speakers from all over the world, talking about our all-time favorite topic, WordPress! 24 sessions. 1 session every hour, on the hour, for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>WordSesh will be live streamed everywhere using the combination of Google Hangout and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/WordSesh">YouTube&#8217;s live streaming</a>. You can find all things WordSesh at <a href="http://wordsesh.org/">WordSesh.org</a>.  Starting <strong>Saturday, April 13th at 00:00 UTC (Friday, April 12th at 8:00pm for those of you in the Eastern time zone)</strong> &#8211; from a computer near you.</p>\n<p>24 hours of WordPress is a pretty cool thing, but we also know you might need to get a little sleep, don&#8217;t worry! All presentations will be available after the event at <a href="http://wordsesh.org/">WordSesh.org</a> and on the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/WordSesh">WordSesh YouTube page</a>. You can also follow along on the <a href="https://twitter.com/WordSesh">WordSesh Twitter feed</a> and <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23wordsesh&amp;src=hash">#WordSesh hashtag</a>.</p>\n<p>What&#8217;s the best thing about this event? It&#8217;s absolutely <strong>free.</strong> That&#8217;s right &#8211; you can stuff your head full of WordPress facts, without touching your wallet!</p>\n<p>And what is UTC exactly? You can use this link to help you out, and avoid confusion:<br />\n<strong><a href="http://www.worldtimeserver.com/convert_time_in_UTC.aspx">Convert Time</a></strong></p>\n<h3><span style="color: #888888"><strong>How is WebDevStudios involved?</strong></span></h3>\n<p>Kicking off the event will be our very own <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a> with his Partner in crime, <a href="https://twitter.com/dremeda">Dre Armeda</a> with the DradCast. You can see the kick off at 8:00 PM EDT on their <a href="http://dradcast.com/">DradCast website</a> or <a href="http://wordsesh.org/">WordSesh.org</a>. If you haven&#8217;t tuned in yet, <a href="http://dradcast.com/">DradCast</a> is a weekly talk show that showcases all things WordPress and has new guest host every week. It&#8217;s both entertaining to watch AND informative.</p>\n<p>Also, our very own <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a> will be speaking at 2:00 AM EDT about <em>Scoping Projects to Avoid Stress, Headaches &amp; Angry Mobs</em>. If you missed the talk at WordCamp Miami last week, don&#8217;t you fret because you will have another chance this weekend! Tune in to watch it from wherever you are!</p>\n<p>Last, we would like to give a big thank you to our friends over at <a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> for presenting WordSesh and main organizer, <a href="http://scottbasgaard.com/">Scott Basgaard</a>. It&#8217;s going to be a great event!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/11/wordsesh-2013-24-hours-of-wordpress/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:63:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"Migrating WordPress Multisite from a Development URL to Staging or Production URL";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:118:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/04/08/migrating-wordpress-multisite-from-a-development-url-to-staging-